## Component 2: Field Type Dropdown/Selector

### Goal
Replace the native browser dropdown with a custom dropdown that includes icons and descriptions. Each field type should have a visual icon, making it easier to scan and identify. The dropdown should feel like a refined menu, not a clunky system widget.

### Specific HTML/CSS Changes

**Trigger Button:**
```html
<!-- REPLACE native select with: -->
<button type="button" class="field-type-trigger">
    <div class="field-type-trigger-content">
        <span class="field-type-trigger-icon">üìù</span>
        <span>Text</span>
    </div>
    <span class="field-type-trigger-arrow">‚ñº</span>
</button>
```

```css
.field-type-trigger {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: white;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
}

.field-type-trigger:hover {
    border-color: #94a3b8;
}

.field-type-trigger.active {
    border-color: #3b82f6;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1);
}
```

**Dropdown Menu:**
```html
<div class="field-type-dropdown">
    <div class="field-type-option selected">
        <div class="field-type-icon">üìù</div>
        <div class="field-type-info">
            <div class="field-type-name">Text</div>
            <div class="field-type-description">Single line of text</div>
        </div>
        <span class="field-type-check">‚úì</span>
    </div>
    <!-- repeat for each type -->
</div>
```

```css
